symbols.name: sap.sac.df.changeHandler.MultiDimModelChangeHandler
symbols.description: Control to handle changes of sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel. To store the changes in sap.ui.fl.variants.VariantManagement you need to include this change handler control as a dependent somewhere in the view tree for which the variant management is responsible. Each time new data is fetched and the event dataLoaded is fired a new change will be created. The method dataLoaded needs to be called once to register the sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel to the change handler.

symbols.name: sap.sac.df.model.DataProvider
symbols.description:
A data provider is an analytical query exposed via an analytical engine and accessed via InA protocol. It represents a navigable query manager and allows to access and change data. Instances of this class should only be created by the sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel.

Structure of Exposed Data: 


"Name": "",
"DataSourceInfo": { },
"Variables": { }
"Dimensions": { },
"Measures": [ ],
"Messages": [ ]
"AutoFetchEnabled": ""

properties.name: AutoFetchEnabled
properties.description: Indicator if the result set should be fetched automatically. The default value is true.

events.name: dataUpdated
events.description: The dataUpdated event is fired, when a new result set was fetched

events.name: visualizationAdded
events.description: The visualizationAdded event is fired, when a new visualization is added

events.name: visualizationRemoved
events.description: The visualizationRemoved event is fired, when a new visualization is removed

parameters.description: the JSON object containing the persisted state of a data provider to be applied.

symbols.name: sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel
symbols.description:
The multidimensional model allows to access and change data accessed via the InA Protocol. The multidimensional model populate it's exposed data in JSON format via binding to controls.

Structure of Exposed Data: 


"DataProviders": { },
"VariableGroups": { },
"Messages": [ ]

parameters.name: sId
parameters.description: ID for the new control, generated automatically if no ID is given

constructor.description: Constructor for a new MultiDimModel. After model creation you need to wait for the event loaded.

examples.data:
Example: how to add and configure a MultiDimModel via manifest.json 

"MultiDimModel": {
  "type": "sap.sac.df.model.MultiDimModel",
  "preload": true,
  "settings": {
    "clientIdentifier": "",
    "DataProviders": {
      "anyDataProviderName": {
        "dataSourceName": "<>",
        "systemName": "<>",
        "packageName": "<>",
        "schemaName": "<>",
        "dataSourceType": "<>"
      }
    }
  }
}
